 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$a = {{1 - {{\tan }^2}{\theta  \over 2}} \over {{{\sec }^2}{\theta  \over 2}}}$$<br><br>$$b = {{2\tan {\theta  \over 2}} \over {{{\sec }^2}{\theta  \over 2}}}$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $${a^2} + {b^2} = 1$$
<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow $$ $$13({a^2} + {b^2})$$ = 13

